    "description": {
      "en": {
        "provenance": "imported",
        "value": "Over 14,000 people lost their lives and thousands more were the victims of gross human rights violations during the ten-year conflict which began in 1996 and ended with the signing of the Comprehensive Peace Agreement in 2006. IOM Nepal in partnership with OHCHR-Nepal is working with the Ministry of Peace and Reconstruction (MoPR) to develop and implement a comprehensive reparation policy in line with international human rights and humanitarian law standards.  In addition to developing reparations policy, the project will increase the capacity of relevant government agencies including MoPR as well as TRC and COI-D to develop and implement the needed procedures, processes and guidelines including a database essential for the successful implementation of a reparations program."
      },
      "ne": null
